Two Scrabble experts have lifted the lid on how to win at the popular board game - just in time for Christmas.

The experts have revealed that if you fancy winning against your relatives, it's best to make sure at least one of your seven letters is an S.

And words without vowels like brrr, grrl, pfft, and psst will also help you clinch you the title.

According to UK Scrabble expert Barry Grossman, there are at least 100 different ways players can win

